This product includes a small excerpt of the official AP242 EXPRESS
schema — nineteen declarations total, copied (mostly verbatim, two
spots deliberately adapted — see below) from
ap242ed2_dis2_mim_lf_v1.101.exp — ISO TS 10303-442 AP242 "managed model
based 3d engineering", EXPRESS MIM Long Form, v1.101 (2019) — obtained
from the CAx Implementor Forum / MBx Implementor Forum's public EXPRESS
schema resources at https://www.mbx-if.org/home/mbx/resources/express-schemas/.
This excerpt is vendored under
kstep-express/src/main/resources/dev/kstep/express/codegen/ap242-v1-entities.exp
(see that file's own header comment for the exact provenance of each
declaration); it is not the paywalled ISO standard prose (ISO/TS
10303-442) and is not itself kSTEP source code or a build dependency.

Verbatim (copied unmodified): the six V1 entities `product`,
`product_definition`, `product_definition_formation`,
`next_assembly_usage_occurrence`, `approval`, `person_and_organization`;
the three `TYPE` declarations (`identifier`, `label`, `text`); and the
seven supporting `ENTITY` declarations `product_context`,
`product_definition_context`, `approval_status`, `person`,
`organization`, `application_context_element`, `application_context`.

Adapted (not verbatim — deliberate truncations, added for the M2
SUBTYPE-OF-codegen wave so `next_assembly_usage_occurrence`'s SUBTYPE OF
chain resolves): `product_definition_relationship`,
`product_definition_usage`, `assembly_component_usage`.
`product_definition_relationship`'s `relating_product_definition`/
`related_product_definition` are typed `product_definition` here rather
than the real schema's `product_definition_or_reference` SELECT type
(SELECT types have no Kotlin mapping in this codebase and vendoring one
plus its full member-entity list was judged to exceed the "minimal,
gap-driven excerpt" precedent this NOTICE documents); the `SUPERTYPE OF`
clauses of `product_definition_usage`/`assembly_component_usage`/
`application_context_element` are kept verbatim in full but name sibling
entities (`make_from_usage_option`, `multi_level_reference_designator`,
`promissory_usage_occurrence`, `specified_higher_usage_occurrence`,
`quantified_assembly_component_usage`, `product_concept_context`) that
are not themselves vendored here — the same pre-existing treatment
already applied to `product_definition`'s own `SUPERTYPE OF ONEOF` list.
See the schema file's own header comment for the full rationale.

Provenance note: the complete, unmodified schema file is not vendored
in this repository — only the excerpt above. The decision to include
even that excerpt rests on established precedent in the open-source
STEP tooling ecosystem: the STEPcode project (BSD licensed,
https://github.com/stepcode/stepcode) bundles this same MBx-IF-published
AP242 schema family in full
(https://github.com/stepcode/stepcode/tree/develop/data/ap242), without
a separate copyright or license notice attached to the schema file
itself beyond attribution to its ISO document number — the same
attribution pattern followed here. This is not a legal opinion; it is
a documented precedent, offered so a future maintainer or auditor can
evaluate the same evidence rather than trusting an unverified claim.

